# Database safety

Never run destructive database commands unless the user explicitly requests a specific command by name in the current message.

## Forbidden without explicit user request

- `prisma migrate reset`
- `DROP DATABASE` / `DROP TABLE` / `TRUNCATE TABLE`
- `prisma db push --force-reset`
- Any script or SQL whose primary effect is wiping or replacing the whole database
- Deleting migration history to “fix” drift when that risks data loss

## Allowed for schema updates (non-destructive)

- `prisma migrate deploy` — applies pending `ALTER TABLE` / `ADD COLUMN` migrations only
- `prisma migrate dev` — only when the user explicitly asks for a new local migration
- Targeted `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN` with safe defaults
- `prisma db pull` / read-only inspection queries

## When schema and DB are out of sync

1. Diagnose with `prisma migrate status` and read-only checks (e.g. `DESCRIBE Expense`).
2. Prefer `prisma migrate deploy` or a single additive `ALTER TABLE`.
3. Explain clearly; do not reset the database to “fix” the issue.
4. If data seems missing, investigate connection target (local vs VPS/tunnel) before assuming data was deleted.
